cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with cache-aided interference networks, which involve communication and information theory, making cs.IT the most likely category. The network involves transmitters and receivers, which suggests the category cs.NI (networking and internet architecture) as a likely second choice. The paper also proposes a new approach based on combinatorial design, which could fall under cs.SI (social and information networks) or cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with optimizing the cache placement and communication scheme, which could fall under cs.CC (computational complexity).
